        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 11:26PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1125 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Bootleg, or 14 miles northwest of Friona, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Simms, Hereford, and Bootleg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
